title: Finca Monteverde Wush Wush, Colombia
description: Origin Colombia Region Herrera, Tolima Varietal Wush Wush, Gesha, Mokka Process Natural Taste Profile Bubblegum, Raspberry, Peach, Pineapple, Cocoa Sweet peaches, bubblegum and mixed berries like aroma. Distinct flavour of tropical fruits, mango, pineapple and hints of cocoa. Medium-bodied with juicy acidity and a puckering finish that lingers. Australian International Coffee Awards 2019 — Finca Monteverde Wush Wush - Bronze Medal (Pourover, Single Origin) Filter Coffee Coffee Story Just off the coast of Monteverde, Finca Monteverde is a 15-hectare farm cultivating the unique coffee varieties of Red and Yellow Bourbon, Gesha, Wush Wush, and Mocca. It is home to Gilardo Gutierrez and his family where they have over 70 years of expertise and experience growing coffee. Known for their impeccable attention to detail, their coffee cherries are harvested at optimal ripeness and undergo controlled fermentation for up to 36 hours. title: Anasora Guji, Ethiopia (Natural)
description: Origin Ethiopia Region Oromia, Guji Varietal Ethiopian Heirloom Process Natural Taste Profile Floral, Lemon Zest, Cherry, White Peach, Winey, Long Finish For Roasting Schedule & Delivery click here . For Self Pickup Please wait for status update from our team before making your way to collect your order. *Online orders are processed at a different location. Coffee Story This coffee originates from Anasora , a district located in the famous Guji region of Ethiopia . The farm is situated alongside river Turo and elevated on extreme altitudes of up to 2350 metres. The high altitude allows a longer time for the coffee cherries to mature before harvesting, therefore contributing to the increased sweetness in the coffee. We adore this lovely coffee for its distinctive mango and red floral notes. We also taste lemon zest and blueberry, and its flavours are even more pronounced when cooled. This is definitely one of our favourite coffees for hand brew and is currently served in-house at both c

title: Reusable Metal Straws
description: Set includes: 2 x Stainless Steel Metal Straws ( 215mm x 6mm) 1x Cleaning Brush 1 x Cotton Drawstring Pouch Many of our single use plastic straws end up in our drains, canals and eventually the oceans, harming our water system, wildlife and marine life. To minimise the number of single use plastic straws and our carbon footprint, Reusable Metal straws are now available at B&B for everyone! Let's be part of the solution, not part of the pollution by starting with carrying our own reusable straw!

title: Finca San Jacinto, Honduras
description: Origin Honduras Region Marcala, La Paz Varietal Typica Process Natural Taste Profile Blueberry, Red Cherry, Melon, Stone fruit, Jasmine Tea Coffee Story This coffee originates from San Jacinto , a small farm in Honduras . Isaura Martinez has dedicated her life to the cultivation of coffee and her greatest inspiration is her father, Antonio Martinez. Her father is a visionary coffee producer and is recognised as a legend in Opatoro, La Paz. He has taught her the practices of processing, drying and storing coffee, which she has since developed her own methods and is traditionally known for her washed process coffees. Isaura, however, took a leap of faith with this exquisite coffee and used a natural process instead. This results in an exclusive micro-lot that is inviting, flavourful and aromatic with lots of fruity flavours. We enjoy this coffee for its blueberry, red cherry, melon and stone fruit tasting notes. Medium-bodied, you will also get a cup with a lingering dark jasmine tea-lik

title: Los Nisperos Chirripo, Costa Rica, Filter Roast
description: Origin Costa Rica Region Chirripo Varietal Red Catuai, Caturra Process Natural Taste Profile Pineapple, Cherry, Grape Candy, Cognac Proudly Roasted by Brawn & Brains Coffee Our very own roastery located in Bedok JTC Bedok Food City, Singapore, is where all the magic happens. With 9 years of coffee roasting experience, we have introduced an extensive range of espresso and filter roast coffee over the years, all of which are seasonal and from various coffee producing origins. Our roastery team has also developed our very own roasting recipe to best bring out the distinct flavours and highlights of each coffee Roasting with integrity, consistency and producing quality coffee is of utmost importance to us and one of our Company’s core values. As such, we only use 100% Arabica coffee. Our roasting service is also available for wholesale and w e are certified and registered with Singapore Food Agency (SFA) as a licensed wholesale distributor.
